OL,3,CWales beaten 4-2 by Belgium as World
OL,4,CCup hopes suffer hammer blow
OL,6,FThe result completely changed the
OL,7,Fcomplexion of Monday night's clash at
OL,8,Fthe Cardiff City Stadium and presented
OL,9,FCraig Bellamy's side with a
OL,10,Fmouthwatering opportunity.
OL,12,FFans filed into the ground with hope.
OL,13,FBut Wales were no longer playing to
OL,14,Fkeep their hopes of automatic
OL,15,Fqualification alive, they were playing
OL,16,Fto take control of the group.
OL,18,FThe start was electric, just as
OL,19,FBellamy hoped it would be.
