OL,3,CWales beaten 4-2 by Belgium as World
OL,4,CCup hopes suffer hammer blow
OL,6,FWales were everything they weren't at
OL,7,FWembley, full of energy, tenacity and
OL,8,Faccuracy.
OL,10,FNeco Williams found space in the box
OL,11,Fon the half turn, the backheel that
OL,12,Ffollowed from David Brooks snuck
OL,13,Fagonisingly wide.
OL,15,FBelgium were misplacing passes, the
OL,16,Fstadium was alive with anticipation
OL,17,Fevery time Wales went forward.
OL,19,FThere were frustrated cries for a
OL,20,Fpenalty when Brooks was hauled down in
OL,21,Fthe box. They were soon forgotten.
