OL,3,CWales beaten 4-2 by Belgium as World
OL,4,CCup hopes suffer hammer blow
OL,6,FFive minutes after Wales' fast start,
OL,7,Fa hopeful pass was dinked in the Wales
OL,8,Fbox. It hit the hand of Ethan Ampadu,
OL,9,Fwho was about a yard away from where
OL,10,Fit was kicked. The midfielder's arm
OL,11,Fwas outstretched and that's what did
OL,12,Ffor him.
OL,14,FAs soon as VAR intervened, the
OL,15,Fawarding of a penalty felt inevitable.
OL,16,FReferee Daniel Siebert only took one
OL,17,Flook before pointing to the spot.
OL,19,FFor his protestations, Bellamy was
OL,20,Fbooked and Kevin De Bruyne sent Karl
OL,21,FDarlow the wrong way.
