OL,3,CWales beaten 4-2 by Belgium as World
OL,4,CCup hopes suffer hammer blow
OL,6,FAs frenetic as this game was, 2-1 felt
OL,7,Frecoverable. But 3-1 did not and Wales
OL,8,Fwere hanging on.
OL,10,FThere was a flourish at the end of the
OL,11,Ffirst half as Jordan James' half-
OL,12,Fvolley was well saved by Courtois. And
OL,13,FHarry Wilson got caught in two minds
OL,14,Fafter latching onto a delicious pass
OL,15,Ffrom Ethan Ampadu.
OL,17,FBut a half that had started with
OL,18,Fcrackle and fizz had fallen flat.
OL,19,FBelgium deserved their lead.
