OL,3,CWales beaten 4-2 by Belgium as World
OL,4,CCup hopes suffer hammer blow
OL,6,FNathan Broadhead benefitted from some
OL,7,Flazy defending to fire Wales back
OL,8,Fwithin striking distance. But
OL,9,Fimmediately from the restart, Belgium
OL,10,Ftore up the far touchline and Trossard
OL,11,Fsmashed in his side's fourth.
OL,13,FIt's a result that puts Wales' fate
OL,14,Fback out of their hands. They must now
OL,15,Fwin their final two games against
OL,16,FLiechtenstein and North Macedonia, and
OL,17,Fhope Belgium slip up.
